  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1979-09-20", 
    "text": "Government Contractors' Product Liability Act of 1979 - Includes periods of military service in computing any period of limitation on the filing of an action or other proceeding to enforce any liability of a supplier of a product to the Government with respect to such product. Makes the Government liable as indemnitor for any loss of such a supplier as a result of the supplier's liability arising from a characteristic of a product if such characteristic is required by Government specifications. Declares that the United States consents to be sued for indemnity under this Act in a court of appropriate jurisdiction. Requires any product supplied to a foreign government under a Federal program to be considered a product supplied to the United States Government for purposes of this Act."
  }, 
